Map Format:
	Header:
		Magic number - 5 bytes - ASCII "ZRM2D"
		Format version - 3 bytes
		Number of extension headers - 4 bytes
		32-bit hash of contents to follow - 4 bytes
	Extension format:
		Type - 4 bytes
		Length (in bytes) - 4 bytes
		(Length) bytes which are defined by the particular type of ext. header

Extension types (ZRM2D v0.0.0:1):
	Tileset descriptor: Type = 1 base10
		filname - null-terminated string

	Pages Section: Type = 2 base10
		Number of pages - 4 bytes
		Set of pages:
			Position x/y - 2 bytes * 2
			Tiles ( row major):
				Tile index -- 2 bytes (1 byte tileset, 1byte tile)

	Entities Section: Type = 3 base10
		Number of entities - 4 bytes
		Set of entities:
			Entity type - 2 bytes
			Length of data - 2 bytes ( excludes these 4 bytes thus far )
			ENTITY_STATE - x bytes, depending on entity type/state
	

	
